<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 6:25PM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Medina,
northeastern Frio and northwestern Atascosa Counties through 715 PM
CDT...
At 625 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North Pearsall, or 7 miles north of Pearsall, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pearsall, Devine, Poteet, Natalia, North Pearsall, Moore, Bigfoot,
Schattel, Iuka, Kyote, Amphion, Rossville and Three Oaks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
